==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Welsher
<hw>Welsh"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who cheats at a
horse race; one who bets, without a chance of being able to pay; one who
receives money to back certain horses and absconds with it.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>welcher</asp>.]</altsp> <mark>[Slang,
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Welshman</ent>⟦br⟧
